  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and analyze cost comparison</li><li>Obtaining quotations, liaising and negotiate with sub-contractors and suppliers</li><li>Responsible for measuring quantities and taking off</li><li>Prepare Variation Orders, claims, final accounts, settlement and sub-contractor payments</li><li>Strong understanding of construction and engineering principles.</li><li>Proficiency in cost estimation and quantity takeoff techniques.</li><li>Knowledge of relevant construction contracts and procurement processes.</li><li>Analytical skills to evaluate and manage project costs effectively.</li><li>Attention to detail to ensure accuracy in cost calculations and reporting.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree / Diploma in Civil Engineering, Building or its equivalent</li><li>2 years and above experience as QS in main-con companies</li><li>Proven ability in contract negotiation, contract administration & variation orders</li><li>Familiarity with relevant software and tools used in quantity surveying, such as cost estimating software and project management applications.</li><li>Able to work independently, be meticulous, analytical with excellent problem-solving skills, proactive, a good team player & able to meet tight deadlines</li><li>Preferably with working experiences in Government projects</li><li>5 days work week</li></ul>",
